theorem tendsto_of_forall_preimage {f : α → β} (h : ∀ s, is_compact s → is_compact («expr ⁻¹' » f s)) :
    tendsto f (cocompact α) (cocompact β) := fun s hs =>
  match mem_cocompact.mp hs with
  | ⟨t, ht, hts⟩ => mem_map.mpr (mem_cocompact.mpr ⟨«expr ⁻¹' » f t, h t ht, by simpa using preimage_mono hts⟩)
#align tendsto_of_forall_preimage tendsto_of_forall_preimage
is_compact_preimage:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⁻¹' » -/
/-- If the codomain is Hausdorff, preimages of compact sets are compact under a cocompact
continuous map. -/
theorem is_compact_preimage [t2_space β] (f : cocompact_map α β) ⦃s : set β⦄ (hs : is_compact s) :
    is_compact («expr ⁻¹' » f s) :=
  by
  obtain ⟨t, ht, hts⟩ :=
    mem_cocompact'.mp
      (by
        simpa only [preimage_image_preimage, preimage_compl] using
          mem_map.mp
            (cocompact_tendsto f <| mem_cocompact.mpr ⟨s, hs, compl_subset_compl.mpr (image_preimage_subset f _)⟩))
  exact is_compact_of_is_closed_subset ht (hs.is_closed.preimage <| map_continuous f) (by simpa using hts)
#align is_compact_preimage is_compact_preimage
